						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If you know you'll not display the object, just perform game logic on it and nothing else.</div>
<br />Well, if you KNOW it, this couldn't prevent your game to have flickers and slowdowns, but avoid to have BOTH at the same time, right ?
<br />But I'd have trouble to figure how to KNOW your player isn't gonna to be displayed AT ALL because of other objects on the same scanline with higher priority. The calculation to do this could be slower than just setup the sprite of your player.
<br />However, this is possible and quite easy to KNOW if it is not going to be displayed because the OAM is already full, wich is rather rare, but you can then limit the slowdowns. I think the game I'm coding does pretty much that.</div>

					
